edu.stanford.nlp.time

Class SUTime

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.nlp.time.SUTime

  • public class SUTime
extends Object
    SUTime is a collection of data structures to represent various temporal concepts and operations between them. Different types of time expressions:
    • Time - A time point on a time scale In most cases, we only know partial information (with a certain granularity) about a point in time (8:00pm)
    • Duration - A length of time (3 days)
    • Interval - A range of time with start and end points
    • Set - A set of time: Can be periodic (Friday every week) or union (Thursday or Friday)

    Use TimeAnnotator to annotate documents within an Annotation pipeline such as CoreNLP. Use SUTimeMain for standalone testing.

    Author:
    Angel Chang
